The Gunners’ need for defensive cover has heightened following a hamstring injury to Kieran Gibbs that will rule him out for the next three weeks.

And Arsenal's defence looked far from secure in the 2-2 draw with Everton at Goodison Park. 

As  revealed last Wednesday, Manolas is a strong contender to fill the vacancy left by Vermaelen.

And Arsenal are pushing hard to complete a deal by September 1.

